$Id: NEWS,v 1.4 2003/04/14 23:35:49 james Rel james $

1.4: (13th September 2004)
	- security vulnerability to crafted reverse DNS names (Jack)
	- fix build errors on Solaris 9 Intel (Schonborn)

1.3: (15th April 2003)
	- add --timeout to terminate on idle (Radusch),
	- daemon mode to use syslog not stderr (Ekenberg),
	- add verbose data dumping in hex (Ekenberg).

1.2: (11th September 2001)
	- now becomes a daemon by default (Holzleitner/Ekenberg), 
	- includes RPM packaging files (Holzleitner),
	- fixes --once (Radusch).

1.1: (4th January 2001)
	- allows binding to local interface address (roc).
	- proper handling of SIGPIPE to prevent connection reset aborts,
	- minor changes to command line argument processing.
